and how you sort of counter that. Have you got a really good value proposition that says,

00:15:20.919 --> 00:15:25.479
this is why it's really important to eventually become polyglot for your folks?

00:15:26.119 --> 00:15:38.840
Mm-hmm. Okay, so in terms of the skilling process, we use DataCamp as a learning platform

00:15:42.919 --> 00:15:50.200
to do the data science trick there, just to have a harmonized set of skills and

00:15:50.280 --> 00:15:58.440
and that people just talk about the functions in the same way, things like that. So that's

00:15:58.440 --> 00:16:07.000
helpful just to streamline the actual coding. We have our own helper packages that interface with

00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:15.000
our infrastructure at various points in both languages. So everybody who joins just gets an

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:21.559
introduction there, and then we'll have just the usual onboarding process within the projects

00:16:21.559 --> 00:16:31.000
that gets the introduction to the code and the specifics of the project. I don't have the feeling

00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:36.599
that I really get pushback, so maybe the pushback is more subtle and I just don't read it right.

00:16:37.400 --> 00:16:42.119
Of course, we're joking about that. So there's the Python team, and then there's the R team,

00:16:42.119 --> 00:16:47.799
and we make our jokes about the one true language, but they're jokes in my opinion.

00:16:49.159 --> 00:16:58.200
They're not really, really serious. We had an initial phase where we had to discuss with

00:16:58.200 --> 00:17:02.280
the rest of the organization, especially, of course, with our T colleagues who are very

00:17:02.280 --> 00:17:10.040
Java-oriented. There is a new data science department who wants to do stuff in R, which is

00:17:10.040 --> 00:17:18.760
strange, and Python, which is not so strange, but still not on the radar, or hasn't been on the

00:17:18.760 --> 00:17:26.119
radar. That's a few years ago, of course, now it's standard. But that wasn't really pushback,

00:17:26.119 --> 00:17:33.640
but it was a new discussion and a more fundamental one. And you asked for the value proposition.

